	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=177838><span id=Scholar>Senbik</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>45 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Lunatic,<br><br>I've seen you using the &quot;more is better, how can it not be?!&quot; opinion before.&nbsp;&nbsp;But when you are using that, are you considering that more melee gear has str/sta/dex over int?  I think you'd have to factor in the difficulty of raising those stats.  Some of the SK only armor (sentient to name one suit) has decent int, but not many lowbies that are new to the game will be able to acquire such a suit of armor before about 30-40.  Some SK weapons have int as well, such as MoSS, but again, those are a bit pricey for someone starting the game as a shadow knight.  Just my 2cp.</p>&nbsp;<br>Senbik -- Gnomish Shadow Knight of Bertoxxulous.<br>Vindayan -- Dark Elven Shadow Knight of Innoruuk.</td></td></tr>
