	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.12]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well first, I have to say on Veeshan Sentient Armor is 200pp per piece, making it the cheapest twink option along with Crusty and Ry`Gorr.&nbsp;&nbsp;Altely anything that doesn't drop off 55+ group encounters is dropping in value fast (can I blame the Bazaar?).  So twinking with Sentient is a real possability.<br><br>Next there are several good back items that add INT (up to 5 points), there are cheap jewelry options for INT and the MoSS is so reduculously cheap on my server I let 1 rot this past weekend while hunting in COM.<br><br>INT vs Regen.  Wow, that's a reach.  Iksar, if created with this in mind can have plenty of INT and still keep decent STR/STA.  Regen is great for the low end game.  I keep an Iksar Ceremonial BP just for twinks now to PL them thru lvl 20.  However at lvl 50 8 HP's a tick regen isn't worth anything (try having someone cast regen on you and see if you even see your life bar move).  Regen should actually balance out with the Race penalty becasue you can level to the 30's that much faster with it.  As for high mana being a disadvantage, never.  Medding between fights is a safety issue to ensure you have mana for adds, resists, etc, but high mana for me means fewer deaths (so faster XP).<br><br>I really don't like this question.  It's very much 1 answer at lvl 20 and another at lvl 60.  At lvl 20 a Regen BP would have doubled my leveling with less downtime to heal.  At lvl 56 regen won't keep me alive during at AE battle, but I have enough mana to keep myself full life with Taps.  So if you like your Iksar great, enjoy the regen and look for +INT items.  If you don't like the lack of mana make a new 1 and try that a while.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
